# Directory Organization

## Required layout
- Keep all routes under `src/app` with route groups for domains (`(_home)`, `(classes)`, `(students)`, `(appointments)`).
- Use `_actions` for server actions, `_components` for UI, `_context` for providers local to a route group.
- Keep shared infrastructure in `src/lib` (Prisma client, cross-cutting runtime modules).
- Keep database contract in `prisma/schema.prisma` and deterministic seed data in `prisma/seeds/**`.

## Domain-first boundaries
- Prefer domain folders over generic folders.
- Do not import deep route internals across unrelated route groups unless extracted to `src/app/lib` or `src/lib`.

## Naming conventions
- Use `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx` only for App Router semantics.
- Name components by feature purpose (`StudentDashboard.tsx`, `CreateAppointment.tsx`).
- Keep conversion/utility modules in `src/app/lib` with descriptive names.

## Change policy
- New feature = new domain folder structure first, then code.
- Avoid mixing server and client concerns in the same file unless required by Next.js conventions.
